00:18:02,230 --> 00:18:05,640
For putting me in this body, that is!

264
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:21,150
You fool! Get off me!

265
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:35,340
Rick!

266
00:18:36,330 --> 00:18:37,390
It can't be...!

267
00:18:38,260 --> 00:18:39,930
Rick!

268
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:49,610
Rick! Rick!

269
00:18:49,610 --> 00:18:50,940
Why?

270
00:18:54,060 --> 00:18:55,030
Rick?

271
00:19:03,630 --> 00:19:06,580
Mom saved me.

272
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:14,960
This is eye medicine.

273
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,050
Medicine?

274
00:19:16,660 --> 00:19:20,580
Your mother's eyes 
must have been ill.

275
00:19:20,580 --> 00:19:25,310
But she didn't want to worry you, 
so she pretended that she could still see.

276
00:19:25,770 --> 00:19:26,980
Come to mention it,

277
00:19:26,980 --> 00:19:31,980
she said she wasn't able to do enough for her children because of her body.

278
00:19:31,980 --> 00:19:35,070
But on the inside, it must have been considerably harder for her.

279
00:19:36,430 --> 00:19:38,380
She couldn't see.

280
00:19:38,380 --> 00:19:39,030
Then...

281
00:19:45,090 --> 00:19:48,950
Leo! Rick! Leo! Rick!

282
00:19:54,030 --> 00:19:57,050
Mom couldn't see.

283
00:19:57,760 --> 00:19:59,540
She was looking for us

284
00:19:59,540 --> 00:20:01,500
and went into the children's room.

285
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:03,550
Mom...

286
00:20:12,150 --> 00:20:15,560
What's the meaning of this?! 
I thought I was hired by the military!

287
00:20:16,050 --> 00:20:19,070
So why was there a State Alchemist getting in our way?!

288
00:20:19,490 --> 00:20:21,320
Hey, are you listening to me?!

289
00:20:21,670 --> 00:20:24,320
Would you say something—

290
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,840
Where are you going now?

291
00:20:37,210 --> 00:20:41,640
There are others who make their way 
while avoiding pursuit.

292
00:20:42,180 --> 00:20:44,420
I think we shall go visit them.

293
00:20:44,420 --> 00:20:46,930
Al, thanks for everything!

294
00:20:46,930 --> 00:20:50,350
From now on, I'm going to go on living, holding memories of my mother dear.

295
00:20:50,770 --> 00:20:51,660
Uh-huh.

296
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:55,430
I, too, am going to hold my memories.

297
00:20:55,430 --> 00:20:58,660
Really... hold them as real memories.

298
00:20:58,660 --> 00:21:00,360
Alphonse Elric...

299
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:02,060
Earlier,

300
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:03,860
I saw something in you.

301
00:21:04,850 --> 00:21:07,280
The tears that you couldn't see in your own eyes.

302
00:21:08,750 --> 00:21:11,830
You are human.

303
00:21:12,470 --> 00:21:14,080
Scar-san...

304
00:21:15,660 --> 00:21:18,080
Scar! Tell me one thing.

305
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:22,530
Did you, the people of Ishbala, have a Philosopher's Stone,

306
00:21:22,530 --> 00:21:24,170
which the military was after?

307
00:21:24,540 --> 00:21:25,940
No.

308
00:21:25,940 --> 00:21:27,730
We sought a Philosopher's Stone,

309
00:21:27,730 --> 00:21:31,180
to protect ourselves from being destroyed by the military that was after us.

310
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:34,680
So did you make one? 
A Philosopher's Stone?

311
00:21:37,370 --> 00:21:38,190
Get us underway.

312
00:21:38,560 --> 00:21:41,320
H-Hey! Hold on a minute!

313
00:21:41,590 --> 00:21:43,860
Brother, let him go.

314
00:21:43,860 --> 00:21:46,680
Those people need him.

315
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:59,500
Al, shall we get going?

316
00:22:00,730 --> 00:22:01,460
Mm-hmm.

317
00:22:03,060 --> 00:22:07,510
Now that I think about it, we always argued over the dumbest things, huh?

318
00:22:07,510 --> 00:22:10,960
Mm-hmm, like who had top or bottom of the bunk beds, and stuff.

319
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:13,170
I lost that one.

320
00:22:13,170 --> 00:22:16,750
And when we fought over toys, I won.

321
00:22:16,750 --> 00:22:18,900
We fought over candy too, huh?

322
00:22:18,900 --> 00:22:22,020
Ah, I never did win.

323
00:22:22,020 --> 00:22:26,890
You squeeze your right hand, as if to reassure yourself

324
00:22:22,020 --> 00:22:26,890
tashikameru you ni nigirishimeta migite

325
00:22:26,890 --> 00:22:31,740
Go on, take those annoying rules and dash them away!

326
00:22:26,890 --> 00:22:31,740
uzattai housoku o buchikowashite yuke

327
00:22:31,890 --> 00:22:36,880
If it comes down to having to rest your wounded feet,

328
00:22:31,890 --> 00:22:36,880
kizutsuita ashi o yasumaseru gurai nara

329
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:41,770
you've gotta keep moving forward, if only just a step!

330
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:41,770
tatta ippo demo koko kara susume

331
00:22:42,310 --> 00:22:46,540
We've pushed our way

332
00:22:42,310 --> 00:22:46,540
through the twisting winds

333
00:22:42,310 --> 00:22:46,540
yuganda kaze o kaki wakete

334
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:51,670
and gotten beyond the cold sky

335
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:51,670
tsumetai sora o oikoshite

336
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:58,440
Yet we still continue to wander

337
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:58,440
soredemo mada samayoi tsuzuketeru

338
00:23:01,980 --> 00:23:06,610
We always find ourselves crying out

339
00:23:01,980 --> 00:23:06,610
bokura wa itsudemo sakenderu

340
00:23:06,610 --> 00:23:11,950
Just continuing to believe is not the answer

341
00:23:06,610 --> 00:23:11,950
shinji tsuzukeru dake ga kotae janai

342
00:23:11,950 --> 00:23:16,660
We must bare our weaknesses and wounds,

343
00:23:11,950 --> 00:23:16,660
yowasa mo kizu mo sarake dashite

344
00:23:16,660 --> 00:23:21,340
and continue to struggle,

345
00:23:16,660 --> 00:23:21,340
or nothing will ever turn out!

346
00:23:16,660 --> 00:23:21,340
mogaki tsuzukenakereba hajimaranai

347
00:23:21,340 --> 00:23:29,040
Break on through to the other side of the door!

348
00:23:21,340 --> 00:23:29,040
tsukiyabure tobira no mukou e

349
00:23:29,160 --> 00:23:34,640
To the other side of the door!

